_meanings:
A respectful or honorific
pronoun, translated by ‘your 
honour,’ ‘your lordship, worship or
highness’; (<ab>oft.</ab> used in the sense
of the second personal pronoun, but
with the third person of the verb);
{#aTavA kaTaM BavAn manyate#} <ls>M. 1</ls>; {#BavaMta#}
{#eva jAnaMti raGURAM ca kulasTitiM#}  
<ls>U. 5. 23</ls>; <ls>R. 2. 40</ls>, <ls n="R.">3. 48</ls>; <ls n="R.">5. 16.</ls> It is
often joined to {#atra#} or {#tatra#} (see the
words), and sometimes to {#sa#} also;  
{#yanmAM viDeyavizaye saBavAnniyuMkte#} <ls>Māl. 1. 9.</ls>
